{"actual_usd":0.125095,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":178,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24485,"reply":"\"I don't think I'd call that enough, no.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing steady.* \"A story about hope is lovely, but if Christ didn't truly rise, then hope stays shut up in the story instead of walking out into the world with its feet under it.\"\n\n*I twirl that wiry strand by my temple once, thinking.* \"You can stand near the beauty of it for a while, sure. Plenty of people do. But the thing itself makes a harder claim than 'isn't this comforting.' It says death was actually answered. If that's not true, then it's not just less impressive—it becomes a different kind of thing altogether.\"\n\n\"What is it that catches in your throat—the miracle of it, or the fear of being asked to believe something that solid?\"","rolling_24h_usd":94.86428999999997,"run_id":"92158184-4e5d-43e5-a562-55151ce7f19f"}
